# Goals

The point of this class is to introduce nessicary skills to make community impact and develop intellectual property through software development. The expectation is that you arive green.

# Special Topics
- Image Processing (Image Segmentation)
- Language Processing (Genius Lyrics Study)
- Audio Processing (Spectral Power Subtraction)
 - Data Journalism / Reporting
  - Data Visualization (MinardMap.org)
  - 
- Crowdsourcing (HappyWhale)
- Secrets
  - Steganography (Demo)
  - Cryptography (Historical Cyphers)
  * Privacy Systems (Tor)
- Artificial Intelligence
  - Symbolic
    - Game Solvers (Tic-Tac-Toe)
    - Transformers (Therapy)
  - Statistical
    - Classification
    - Generative
    - Regression
- Security & Privacy Systems
  - Password Crackers (Rainbow Tables, John the Ripper)
  - Network Security (Wireshark & WEP cracking)
- Opressive Systems of Scale
  - Snowden Files
  - Wepons of Math Destruction (Employment Personality Tests)
  * Free Speech and Attention Systems on Social Media
- Scientific Computing
- Internet of Things
- Wearable Technology (AdaFruit)

The throughline of this course is to build a Search Engine 

# Topics

- Shell (1 Week)
 - shell vs GUI
 - Folder navigation
 - Bash
 - man pages
 - apropos
- Computers (1 Week)
 - Circuit Operations
 - What is machine code?
 - What is abstraction
- IDE setup (Atom)
- Version Control & Remote Work (1 Week)
 - Ticketing Systems
 - Time Tracking / Management
 - Nessicary Working Environment
 - Git for personal projects
 - Git for collaboration
- Python as a CLI tool (2 Weeks)
 - Statements
 - Control Flow
 - Functions
 - Error handling
 - Logging
 - Classes
 - Packages
- Python as a Analysis Tool (2 day)
 - Jupyter & non-sequential workflows
 - matplotlib
 - using pandas
 - using numpy (& array programming)
- Typescript & HTML for UX (2 Weeks)
 - Basic DOM
 - Basic UI
 - Document Data/Pipeline Processing
- Sourcing Projects for Community Impact (1 Week)
 - Identifying who needs what information
 - Intro to Threat Modeling as a Concept
 - Identifying sharing as a value add
 - Identifying what can be automated
 - Identifying what is hard
 - Sourcing non-profits and community centers and activities in your area
- Python as a backend (2 Weeks)
 - POST, PUT, GET
 - Basic Networking (telnet style chat)
 - Broadcast vs Direct
 - Flask
 - API design
- Chat applications (2 Days)
- Document Storage
